1
00:00:18,257 --> 00:00:19,697
(Episode 9)

2
00:00:52,201 --> 00:00:54,971
What is that? What are you doing again?

3
00:01:03,193 --> 00:01:05,333
I asked you what you are doing.

4
00:01:09,433 --> 00:01:11,763
I can't decipher. I will delay the judgment.

5
00:01:13,733 --> 00:01:16,763
I don't think you will answer it even if I ask you, so I won't ask.

6
00:01:19,033 --> 00:01:20,263
What's up with her?

7
00:01:20,833 --> 00:01:23,463
Boss! Boss!

8
00:01:23,463 --> 00:01:24,763
Ae Rang ran away.

9
00:01:33,763 --> 00:01:35,563
Where will I find a replacement?

10
00:01:36,263 --> 00:01:37,893
Who's going to perform tonight?

11
00:01:38,833 --> 00:01:40,663
It'd be best if I...

12
00:01:40,663 --> 00:01:42,133
What if your voice cracks again?

13
00:01:48,763 --> 00:01:51,893
Libera, didn't I tell you to give up on becoming a singer?

14
00:01:54,863 --> 00:01:57,563
Don't worry. I've found the perfect replacement.

15
00:01:58,263 --> 00:02:00,033
You found one already?

16
00:02:00,393 --> 00:02:03,163
Of course. It's someone...

17
00:02:03,793 --> 00:02:05,463
refreshingly new.

18
00:02:19,533 --> 00:02:21,133
Let go of me! Right now!

19
00:02:21,233 --> 00:02:24,033
I said I don't want to do it. I'm not going to do it.

20
00:02:24,033 --> 00:02:27,193
Gosh, you're like an uncontrollable beast.

21
00:02:27,793 --> 00:02:30,263
Madam, can't I sing instead?

22
00:02:30,393 --> 00:02:31,693
I can do a good job.

23
00:02:31,963 --> 00:02:32,993
Get out.

24
00:02:36,533 --> 00:02:38,233
Why me, of all people?

25
00:02:38,433 --> 00:02:41,263
I've heard you sing along with Ae Rang before.

26
00:02:42,103 --> 00:02:43,763
- You were pretty good. 
- I was just...

27
00:02:43,863 --> 00:02:45,993
humming along for fun.

28
00:02:47,693 --> 00:02:50,193
If you're worried your cover will be blown, don't worry.

29
00:02:51,393 --> 00:02:53,463
It's been years already.

30
00:02:54,563 --> 00:02:56,663
No one will recognize you even if you dress like a girl.

31
00:02:58,133 --> 00:02:59,163
It'll be just on the stage.

32
00:02:59,563 --> 00:03:02,463
What do you think? I'm not going to force you.

33
00:03:03,133 --> 00:03:06,733
Let me just remind you that you should probably pay back...

34
00:03:07,193 --> 00:03:10,563
Mr. Yoo for taking you in and feeding you all these years.

35
00:03:13,593 --> 00:03:15,963
Gosh, you're making me feel bad.

36
00:03:17,263 --> 00:03:20,533
Fine, I'll do it. Are you happy now?

37
00:03:24,133 --> 00:03:25,933
I can roughly picture you on the stage.

38
00:03:27,993 --> 00:03:31,463
It might actually help our undercover operation.

39
00:03:33,333 --> 00:03:35,663
Undercover operation?

40
00:03:36,063 --> 00:03:37,133
It's none of your business.

41
00:03:37,493 --> 00:03:41,933
Well, let me paint your face now, okay?

42
00:03:48,663 --> 00:03:51,563
Gosh, we're in the red again.

43
00:03:52,833 --> 00:03:54,533
All right, come on out.

44
00:04:56,533 --> 00:04:59,433
Let me introduce our Saturday singer, Anastasia, to you.

45
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:02,463
Gosh, I feel so awkward.

46
00:05:03,093 --> 00:05:05,193
Don't be shy, and come down here.

47
00:05:05,403 --> 00:05:06,663
You should get used to the high heels now.

48
00:05:07,263 --> 00:05:08,263
Darn it.

49
00:05:20,763 --> 00:05:21,933
Be confident.

50
00:05:22,693 --> 00:05:23,793
Try walking forward.

51
00:05:48,263 --> 00:05:51,663
Yul, I look awkward, don't I?

52
00:05:56,163 --> 00:05:59,033
I got feelings for her before he did.

53
00:06:04,663 --> 00:06:08,133
But there's nothing I can do in this life.

54
00:06:23,263 --> 00:06:25,433
(Chicago Typewriter)

55
00:06:27,393 --> 00:06:28,693
Are you done crying now?

56
00:06:30,793 --> 00:06:32,193
If I cry again, will you hug me again?

57
00:06:34,693 --> 00:06:37,093
How can you be so shameless?

58
00:06:44,993 --> 00:06:46,063
Are you that scared?

59
00:06:47,263 --> 00:06:48,333
What do you mean?

60
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:51,263
Are you that scared of seeing your previous life?

61
00:06:55,163 --> 00:06:58,193
Do you want to hear a scary story?

62
00:06:58,793 --> 00:07:00,763
If it's about ghosts, forget it.

63
00:07:01,163 --> 00:07:02,433
It won't scare me at all.

64
00:07:03,093 --> 00:07:05,893
It will. It'll make you very scared.

65
00:07:14,093 --> 00:07:15,363
Once upon a time,

66
00:07:16,593 --> 00:07:18,163
there lived in a countryside...

67
00:07:18,533 --> 00:07:21,433
a woman and her daughter alone.

68
00:07:26,593 --> 00:07:28,163
Mom, am I pretty?

69
00:07:28,933 --> 00:07:30,533
Of course, you are.

70
00:07:31,363 --> 00:07:32,433
Are you serious?

71
00:07:33,033 --> 00:07:36,393
Of course. Seol, you're really pretty.

72
00:07:37,263 --> 00:07:39,033
- Really? 
- Really.

73
00:07:40,593 --> 00:07:42,433
Even if I killed a person?

74
00:07:46,893 --> 00:07:49,393
Seol, what did you just say?

75
00:07:50,263 --> 00:07:52,463
A long time ago, I shot a person.

76
00:08:09,663 --> 00:08:11,393
Play with your friend over there.

77
00:08:11,633 --> 00:08:12,633
Okay.

78
00:08:20,263 --> 00:08:21,633
She's not one of our people.

79
00:08:21,793 --> 00:08:23,233
She doesn't have supernatural powers.

80
00:08:23,633 --> 00:08:25,463
She won't become a shaman, so don't worry.

81
00:08:26,563 --> 00:08:27,933
If it's not supernatural powers...

82
00:08:28,133 --> 00:08:29,193
Well...

83
00:08:30,263 --> 00:08:32,093
Maybe she remembers her previous life.

84
00:08:35,893 --> 00:08:38,133
Her previous life?

85
00:08:39,363 --> 00:08:41,463
I'm just saying.

86
00:08:41,733 --> 00:08:44,133
Anyway, you don't have to worry.

87
00:08:45,063 --> 00:08:48,463
They say your children were your enemies in the previous life.

88
00:08:49,003 --> 00:08:51,863
You probably owed her a lot in your previous life.

89
00:08:51,963 --> 00:08:54,663
In order to work out your karma, take good care of her,

90
00:08:54,863 --> 00:08:56,263
and give her much love.

91
00:09:04,363 --> 00:09:07,003
Mom, don't go.

92
00:09:07,593 --> 00:09:09,193
I'm sorry.

93
00:09:10,393 --> 00:09:12,763
I'll never say such a thing again.

94
00:09:20,503 --> 00:09:22,163
She must have been scared.

95
00:09:23,063 --> 00:09:25,463
Her little kid would wake up from a nap...

96
00:09:26,663 --> 00:09:30,863
and say, "I shouldn't have killed the person,"

97
00:09:31,263 --> 00:09:32,763
crying her heart out.

98
00:09:36,393 --> 00:09:40,463
It wasn't your fault.

99
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:45,763
You were just telling her what you were seeing.

100
00:09:48,263 --> 00:09:51,093
I know. Actually, my mom...

101
00:09:51,733 --> 00:09:53,363
left me for a guy.

102
00:09:55,933 --> 00:09:57,193
Still,

103
00:09:58,363 --> 00:10:01,363
if I were normal, would she have left me?

104
00:10:03,063 --> 00:10:05,733
Would she have sent me to her ex-husband...

105
00:10:05,833 --> 00:10:07,163
as if I'm a package?

106
00:10:09,263 --> 00:10:10,363
I don't think so.

107
00:10:11,263 --> 00:10:13,003
She would have taken me with her.

108
00:10:16,633 --> 00:10:18,093
How is it now?

109
00:10:19,793 --> 00:10:20,893
Do you still see it?

110
00:10:44,733 --> 00:10:47,263
No. Not at all.

111
00:10:47,933 --> 00:10:49,393
I'm completely normal now.

112
00:10:51,793 --> 00:10:52,793
I see.

113
00:10:54,863 --> 00:10:55,933
That's great.

114
00:10:57,063 --> 00:10:59,133
I guess. It's a good thing.

115
00:11:18,263 --> 00:11:19,963
Go in. I'll get going.

116
00:11:21,593 --> 00:11:23,593
If I cry again, will you hug me again?

117
00:11:29,433 --> 00:11:31,733
What's wrong? Do you have a fever again?

118
00:11:42,633 --> 00:11:43,633
You have fever.

119
00:11:44,333 --> 00:11:46,033
Go inside and rest. I'll go now.

120
00:11:52,363 --> 00:11:53,393
Hey, Seol.

121
00:11:55,633 --> 00:11:56,693
I'm...

122
00:11:58,633 --> 00:12:00,633
I'm not scared of you at all.

123
00:12:01,833 --> 00:12:04,593
I don't think you are abnormal.

124
00:12:06,693 --> 00:12:07,893
It's because...

125
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:11,533
I'm even crazier than you.

126
00:12:16,493 --> 00:12:19,763
Also, you are mistaken about something.

127
00:12:22,493 --> 00:12:24,033
I don't abandon people.

128
00:12:24,733 --> 00:12:26,793
I wouldn't accept people if I were to abandon them.

129
00:12:27,893 --> 00:12:28,933
It's because...

130
00:12:33,333 --> 00:12:34,333
I had been...

131
00:12:35,063 --> 00:12:36,633
abandoned before.

132
00:12:41,333 --> 00:12:42,933
So...

133
00:12:44,693 --> 00:12:46,033
So?

134
00:12:48,463 --> 00:12:50,933
So...

135
00:12:54,893 --> 00:12:56,893
I won't abandon Gyun Woo.

136
00:12:56,893 --> 00:12:59,863
I will raise him well. Don't worry.

137
00:12:59,863 --> 00:13:00,863
Bye.

138
00:13:18,833 --> 00:13:23,033
- Look at these people! 
- That's funny.

139
00:13:24,693 --> 00:13:26,333
Sir, it will be over soon.

140
00:13:26,433 --> 00:13:28,933
- Aren't you going to leave? 
- Goodness.

141
00:13:30,263 --> 00:13:31,793
There's a ghost...

142
00:13:32,493 --> 00:13:33,893
living in my house.

143
00:13:34,133 --> 00:13:36,633
This show is really fun. Do you want to watch it with me?

144
00:13:36,933 --> 00:13:40,233
And the ghost loves to watch TV.

145
00:13:41,863 --> 00:13:43,193
- They continue to... 
- Goodness.

146
00:13:43,493 --> 00:13:46,733
There are 101 boys I want to possess.

147
00:13:47,363 --> 00:13:50,563
Which boy do you think will take the center?

148
00:13:50,993 --> 00:13:53,133
He's very interested in the entertainment industry too.

149
00:13:55,063 --> 00:13:57,693
You should've saved So Joon instead of me.

150
00:13:58,593 --> 00:14:00,063
Just now, the leading character...

151
00:14:00,733 --> 00:14:02,163
sacrificed himself...

152
00:14:02,763 --> 00:14:04,533
for his lover.

153
00:14:04,993 --> 00:14:06,193
On top of that,

154
00:14:06,493 --> 00:14:08,563
he also loves romance dramas.

155
00:14:08,993 --> 00:14:10,333
This is so sad.

156
00:14:12,363 --> 00:14:13,833
I want him out of my sight.

157
00:14:15,793 --> 00:14:17,433
The food is ready, sir.

158
00:14:19,033 --> 00:14:22,763
You never watched TV before, but you watch it a lot these days.

159
00:14:23,433 --> 00:14:25,333
That's because I don't have much to do these days.

160
00:14:35,633 --> 00:14:36,733
Let's eat.

161
00:14:38,133 --> 00:14:39,163
Sure.

162
00:14:59,793 --> 00:15:00,863
Ms. Kang.

163
00:15:01,233 --> 00:15:02,233
Yes, sir.

164
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:06,963
Can you prepare one more serving?

165
00:15:07,733 --> 00:15:08,733
Pardon?

166
00:15:09,263 --> 00:15:10,993
Are we expecting a guest?

167
00:15:11,093 --> 00:15:12,093
No.

168
00:15:13,433 --> 00:15:15,563
I'm too bored to eat alone.

169
00:15:16,593 --> 00:15:17,733
Please.

170
00:15:18,593 --> 00:15:19,593
Sure.

171
00:15:27,093 --> 00:15:29,733
Thank you. You may leave now.

172
00:15:31,493 --> 00:15:33,733
Sure. Enjoy your meal.

173
00:15:41,163 --> 00:15:44,733
It's been a long time since someone fixed a meal for me.

174
00:15:45,593 --> 00:15:48,793
I did it only because you were eying on my food.

175
00:15:50,933 --> 00:15:52,263
Don't be too moved by it.

176
00:15:58,263 --> 00:15:59,433
It's good.

177
00:16:00,493 --> 00:16:03,733
It's been 80 years since I had a meal with somebody.

178
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:08,493
When I opened my eyes one day,

179
00:16:08,993 --> 00:16:11,963
I was in another country, indwelled in the typewriter.

180
00:16:13,033 --> 00:16:14,063
I was lonely.

181
00:16:15,363 --> 00:16:17,163
I always missed this land...

182
00:16:17,993 --> 00:16:19,263
where I used to be with my friends.

183
00:16:20,633 --> 00:16:23,263
That's why I was so thrilled...

184
00:16:23,733 --> 00:16:24,933
when I saw you at the cafe in Chicago.

185
00:16:24,933 --> 00:16:27,493
I won't buy your story. Don't sell it.

186
00:16:27,993 --> 00:16:28,993
Okay.

187
00:16:35,693 --> 00:16:38,693
Well, tell me if there's something you want to eat.

188
00:16:39,633 --> 00:16:41,193
I will tell them to prepare it.

189
00:16:44,793 --> 00:16:45,933
Mr. Han!

190
00:16:46,693 --> 00:16:47,733
Mr. Han!

191
00:16:48,533 --> 00:16:49,563
Goodness.

192
00:16:51,463 --> 00:16:54,163
It's not the time to enjoy your meal like this.

193
00:16:57,663 --> 00:16:59,633
The investors are making strange moves.

194
00:17:00,793 --> 00:17:01,793
What are you talking about?

195
00:17:01,793 --> 00:17:04,393
I've been going around busily and begged them to wait...

196
00:17:04,393 --> 00:17:06,233
until the publication resumes.

197
00:17:06,533 --> 00:17:09,393
But suddenly, the investors are calling for an assembly.

198
00:17:10,033 --> 00:17:13,433
Someone must be nudging the investors from behind.

199
00:17:14,733 --> 00:17:18,333
Didn't you tell them we're putting a stop to the project?

200
00:17:18,533 --> 00:17:21,463
The publisher's life depends on it. How can we stop the project?

201
00:17:21,463 --> 00:17:23,263
I made it clear, didn't I?

202
00:17:23,763 --> 00:17:25,263
I said we are stopping this project.

203
00:17:28,333 --> 00:17:31,533
Anyway, you have to step in before this goes out of hand.

204
00:17:31,733 --> 00:17:34,703
If they sue you, 10 million dollars won't be the problem.

205
00:17:34,703 --> 00:17:36,263
You and I will be completely over.

206
00:17:36,763 --> 00:17:39,033
Se Ju, save me this time for once.

207
00:17:39,163 --> 00:17:42,893
I clearly told you my position.

208
00:17:44,033 --> 00:17:46,393
Tell them the truth now,

209
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:48,663
and take the responsibility for your action.

210
00:17:49,063 --> 00:17:52,133
Whatever result we get, I am ready to accept it.

211
00:17:56,063 --> 00:17:57,093
Se Ju.

212
00:17:58,133 --> 00:17:59,163
Se Ju!

213
00:18:02,963 --> 00:18:05,163
Shouldn't you be doing something?

214
00:18:06,593 --> 00:18:09,833
I probably will be paying an unbelievably large penalty.

215
00:18:12,363 --> 00:18:15,563
I will probably lose all my wealth.

216
00:18:16,133 --> 00:18:18,433
You can start publishing the novel again.

217
00:18:18,433 --> 00:18:19,433
I can't do that.

218
00:18:20,263 --> 00:18:23,563
Seol might read the novel and remember the past life.

219
00:18:24,033 --> 00:18:26,863
But Seol read every novel published up until now...

220
00:18:27,203 --> 00:18:29,133
and didn't realize that it's about her past life.

221
00:18:29,793 --> 00:18:32,063
There's no guarantee that she will continue to not figure it out.

222
00:18:33,063 --> 00:18:34,633
To Seol, her past life...

223
00:18:35,793 --> 00:18:37,663
is not a beautiful memory.

224
00:18:38,433 --> 00:18:40,263
It's a trauma for her.

225
00:18:42,163 --> 00:18:43,233
Not everything about her past life...

226
00:18:44,533 --> 00:18:46,933
is traumatic.

227
00:18:47,703 --> 00:18:50,093
She must have good memories too. Why would you only think that?

228
00:18:50,093 --> 00:18:53,263
Why should she remember the things she doesn't have to know?

229
00:18:54,763 --> 00:18:56,133
This novel...

230
00:18:57,333 --> 00:18:59,763
should remain only between us.

231
00:19:07,763 --> 00:19:11,333
Then why don't we do this?

232
00:19:13,433 --> 00:19:15,033
- What is he saying? 
- What?

233
00:19:15,033 --> 00:19:18,333
You should tell us if something is wrong with the project.

234
00:19:18,333 --> 00:19:21,133
I don't know what you heard,

235
00:19:21,433 --> 00:19:23,733
but there's nothing wrong with the project.

236
00:19:23,733 --> 00:19:25,493
- What? 
- What about the rumor?

237
00:19:25,533 --> 00:19:28,663
The rumor that Se Ju stopped writing has spread everywhere.

238
00:19:28,963 --> 00:19:31,033
Do you think it makes sense that there's nothing wrong?

239
00:19:32,633 --> 00:19:34,963
- What are you doing here, Ms. Hong? 
- Oh, right.

240
00:19:35,433 --> 00:19:38,493
I am the largest investor of this project.

241
00:19:39,333 --> 00:19:40,333
What?

242
00:19:40,633 --> 00:19:42,663
As the largest investor,

243
00:19:42,963 --> 00:19:45,363
I have the right to know the facts,

244
00:19:46,063 --> 00:19:50,133
especially when there's a chance the project will be canceled.

245
00:19:51,163 --> 00:19:53,793
Se Ju will resume writing the novel soon.

246
00:19:53,893 --> 00:19:55,633
It's been a little delayed,

247
00:19:55,793 --> 00:19:57,233
but the project will not be canceled.

248
00:19:57,233 --> 00:20:00,963
As investors, we can't just sit and watch.

249
00:20:01,833 --> 00:20:05,203
All right. If the project gets canceled,

250
00:20:05,433 --> 00:20:08,133
we are willing to sue and ask you for a large sum of penalty.

251
00:20:08,233 --> 00:20:11,933
Of course, we might also sue you for...

252
00:20:12,133 --> 00:20:14,233
violation of your duty and fraud.

253
00:20:14,393 --> 00:20:15,393
Ms. Hong.

254
00:20:15,493 --> 00:20:16,533
We demand...

255
00:20:16,633 --> 00:20:21,063
Mr. Han to explain about this rumor himself right now.

256
00:20:21,363 --> 00:20:22,363
Otherwise...

257
00:20:22,363 --> 00:20:23,533
As you asked,

258
00:20:24,203 --> 00:20:26,233
- What? 
- I will explain it myself.

259
00:20:26,233 --> 00:20:27,633
- Is that Mr. Han? 
- It's Mr. Han.

260
00:20:27,633 --> 00:20:28,633
Mr. Han.

261
00:20:29,893 --> 00:20:32,093
What happened?

262
00:20:32,093 --> 00:20:34,593
It's Mr. Han.

263
00:20:34,633 --> 00:20:36,093
Let's see what he has to say.

264
00:20:36,093 --> 00:20:37,893
What's going on?

265
00:20:39,563 --> 00:20:40,633
No way.

266
00:20:40,733 --> 00:20:43,433
Se Ju's novel resumed publication just now.

267
00:20:43,933 --> 00:20:46,093
I see. It's nothing new.

268
00:20:47,063 --> 00:20:49,333
What? Did you already know about it?

269
00:20:49,533 --> 00:20:50,733
Of course.

270
00:20:51,593 --> 00:20:52,593
How?

