He's so weird.

537
00:40:16,069 --> 00:40:17,069
I'm hanging up.

538
00:40:17,569 --> 00:40:19,369
That's Gyeongseong Station.

539
00:40:19,529 --> 00:40:21,529
Can you take a picture of me in front of it?

540
00:40:29,569 --> 00:40:31,469
You should have told me beforehand.

541
00:40:38,399 --> 00:40:40,199
There. Are we good now?

542
00:40:41,199 --> 00:40:43,899
My gosh, you even got that car on the road in the frame.

543
00:40:47,369 --> 00:40:50,569
Cameras these days can certainly capture such fast-moving objects.

544
00:40:51,369 --> 00:40:54,069
You have no idea as you've never experienced technologies like this.

545
00:40:54,669 --> 00:40:55,929
It's very impressive.

546
00:40:57,299 --> 00:40:59,839
Why don't you take Seoul Station out on a date instead?

547
00:41:01,999 --> 00:41:03,529
Oh, my.

548
00:41:06,599 --> 00:41:07,599
Let's take a look.

549
00:41:07,769 --> 00:41:08,969
Welcome.

550
00:41:10,229 --> 00:41:12,099
- You can use these as wallets. 
- I see.

551
00:41:12,599 --> 00:41:13,969
Take a look around.

552
00:41:15,839 --> 00:41:17,169
Hey, how do I look?

553
00:41:19,469 --> 00:41:20,839
How much is this?

554
00:41:24,729 --> 00:41:26,629
(Letter of wishes)

555
00:41:44,669 --> 00:41:45,669
(Please help him be more stable.)

556
00:41:45,669 --> 00:41:48,799
Please help him be more stable.

557
00:42:40,399 --> 00:42:41,599
My gosh, Mr. Han.

558
00:42:41,929 --> 00:42:44,299
The wastewater-filled Cheonggyecheon has changed so much.

559
00:42:44,399 --> 00:42:47,769
Mr. Han, it looks like there is a lantern festival this evening.

560
00:42:47,869 --> 00:42:50,699
Mr. Han, there's a place I'd like to visit later.

561
00:42:50,699 --> 00:42:52,599
Mr. Han, let's eat something first.

562
00:42:52,599 --> 00:42:53,729
Mr. Han, actually...

563
00:42:53,729 --> 00:42:55,829
Gosh, can you stop calling me like that?

564
00:42:56,999 --> 00:43:00,399
I've been calling you like that all along. Then how should I...

565
00:43:00,999 --> 00:43:02,769
Well, I meant...

566
00:43:04,129 --> 00:43:07,299
If you keep calling me like that in public spaces like this,

567
00:43:07,299 --> 00:43:09,129
people will recognize me.

568
00:43:11,829 --> 00:43:13,299
I haven't thought about that.

569
00:43:14,099 --> 00:43:15,669
Then how would you like me to address you?

570
00:43:16,099 --> 00:43:17,129
Han Se Ju?

571
00:43:17,869 --> 00:43:19,199
That would be worse.

572
00:43:20,569 --> 00:43:23,729
Then... How about Ju?

573
00:43:24,999 --> 00:43:27,329
I'd much rather hear you call me Brother.

574
00:43:27,929 --> 00:43:29,669
Then what should I call you?

575
00:43:29,929 --> 00:43:31,099
Shall I really call you Brother?

576
00:43:32,569 --> 00:43:33,799
Can't you hear me?

577
00:43:34,229 --> 00:43:36,499
I refuse to be treated by Hui Young.

578
00:43:38,569 --> 00:43:41,299
Brother sounds great. Let's do that.

579
00:43:42,129 --> 00:43:43,199
Are you serious?

580
00:43:43,399 --> 00:43:45,599
Are we related or what?

581
00:43:45,969 --> 00:43:47,799
You're so weird.

582
00:43:48,199 --> 00:43:50,929
By the way, doesn't it feel like it's gotten quiet around here?

583
00:43:53,129 --> 00:43:55,199
What's the matter? Are you looking for something?

584
00:43:55,499 --> 00:43:56,669
By any chance, have you seen Yoo...

585
00:43:57,829 --> 00:43:59,229
There's no way you would've seen him.

586
00:44:01,969 --> 00:44:02,999
Where did he go?

587
00:44:03,669 --> 00:44:04,999
Wait for me here. I'll be right back.

588
00:44:05,269 --> 00:44:07,569
Wait. Brother, Brother!

589
00:44:07,999 --> 00:44:09,729
Where are you going?

590
00:44:20,999 --> 00:44:22,299
It's really gone.

591
00:44:23,399 --> 00:44:24,669
I told you so.

592
00:44:26,999 --> 00:44:29,069
There was nothing we could do.

593
00:44:30,299 --> 00:44:31,999
Our youth was the only thing we could give.

594
00:44:33,829 --> 00:44:36,369
That's why so many youth perished like that,

595
00:44:37,969 --> 00:44:39,269
but we won.

596
00:44:42,999 --> 00:44:44,329
You better not cry.

597
00:44:44,669 --> 00:44:45,929
I'll ditch you if you do.

598
00:44:48,399 --> 00:44:49,399
I also...

599
00:44:50,299 --> 00:44:52,169
want to live in 2017.

600
00:44:56,099 --> 00:44:58,099
I'd love to live in a world like this.

601
00:45:01,499 --> 00:45:02,869
I told you.

602
00:45:03,229 --> 00:45:04,469
No matter which era you live in,

603
00:45:05,869 --> 00:45:07,369
life is an agony.

604
00:45:09,199 --> 00:45:11,369
There is no such thing as perfect world.

605
00:45:12,469 --> 00:45:14,769
Every era has its own problems...

606
00:45:15,669 --> 00:45:17,099
and things you'd want to resist.

607
00:45:19,229 --> 00:45:21,329
We resist, struggle,

608
00:45:21,869 --> 00:45:24,329
fight, and win.

609
00:45:25,199 --> 00:45:27,899
That's how we shape the world we live in.

610
00:45:33,729 --> 00:45:34,899
Thanks.

611
00:45:36,929 --> 00:45:39,069
Thanks to the youth you guys sacrificed,

612
00:45:40,569 --> 00:45:41,729
we can live in a world like this now.

613
00:45:43,369 --> 00:45:45,469
Pass this message along to the youth of the time.

614
00:45:47,199 --> 00:45:48,429
You fought hard.

615
00:45:49,569 --> 00:45:51,129
And I thank them...

616
00:45:52,569 --> 00:45:53,629
for creating this world for us.

617
00:46:00,569 --> 00:46:01,699
You fought hard too.

618
00:46:03,929 --> 00:46:06,799
You were one of the youth of the time.

619
00:46:12,369 --> 00:46:13,469
Brother!

620
00:46:14,499 --> 00:46:16,929
Gosh, what are you thinking?

621
00:46:17,599 --> 00:46:18,969
You can't even hear me.

622
00:46:19,829 --> 00:46:21,969
And there's another one of the youth.

623
00:46:21,969 --> 00:46:24,429
Don't you think you need a hearing aid?

624
00:46:25,199 --> 00:46:26,199
Mr. Han.

625
00:46:27,729 --> 00:46:29,129
I'd like to ask a favor of you.

626
00:46:34,199 --> 00:46:35,999
To the left. A little bit more.

627
00:46:36,999 --> 00:46:37,999
Is this good?

628
00:46:39,769 --> 00:46:41,399
A little more.

629
00:46:42,099 --> 00:46:43,669
Gosh, you're so fussy.

630
00:46:44,369 --> 00:46:45,369
Like this?

631
00:47:06,299 --> 00:47:09,169
Do you mind taking a photo of me and Seol?

632
00:47:09,999 --> 00:47:11,069
A photo?

633
00:47:11,899 --> 00:47:14,899
You won't even be visible. Why do you want to take a photo?

634
00:47:16,829 --> 00:47:17,869
I know.

635
00:47:18,399 --> 00:47:21,729
But I still want a photo of myself with her.

636
00:47:22,499 --> 00:47:23,599
Would it be okay?

637
00:47:34,129 --> 00:47:35,529
Give me a bigger smile.

638
00:47:57,769 --> 00:47:58,999
Oh, excuse me.

639
00:47:59,729 --> 00:48:01,599
- Could you take a picture of us? 
- Sure.

640
00:48:01,599 --> 00:48:02,599
Thank you.

641
00:48:06,129 --> 00:48:09,999
Okay. 1, 2, 3.

642
00:48:28,171 --> 00:48:29,171
Are you sad?

643
00:48:31,671 --> 00:48:33,801
Does the fact that you couldn't capture the moment...

644
00:48:34,571 --> 00:48:36,901
with Seol in a photo make you sad?

645
00:48:38,801 --> 00:48:42,071
Well, I'd be lying if I told you that I'm not sad at all.

646
00:48:42,271 --> 00:48:43,271
I'm okay though.

647
00:48:44,041 --> 00:48:48,371
Even though it's not visible, the memories will last forever.

648
00:48:48,801 --> 00:48:50,071
You're bluffing again.

649
00:48:52,201 --> 00:48:53,201
I'm glad.

650
00:48:53,771 --> 00:48:57,971
She's still jolly, healthy, and brave. She seems happy too.

651
00:49:00,201 --> 00:49:02,201
She's trying very hard to appear that way.

652
00:49:03,571 --> 00:49:05,871
Haunted by the memories of her past life,

653
00:49:06,671 --> 00:49:08,341
she even had to give up her dream.

654
00:49:09,141 --> 00:49:10,541
It's not exactly a happy life.

655
00:49:11,541 --> 00:49:12,971
That is too bad.

656
00:49:13,701 --> 00:49:16,001
Hadn't she quit shooting, she would certainly have...

657
00:49:16,201 --> 00:49:17,871
made a name for herself as a markswoman.

658
00:49:22,571 --> 00:49:23,901
I'm curious about something.

659
00:49:25,641 --> 00:49:26,771
How did Su Hyeon...

660
00:49:27,941 --> 00:49:29,471
come to learn how to shoot?

661
00:49:33,501 --> 00:49:36,841
The success of Yun Bong Gil's bombing operation in Shanghai...

662
00:49:36,941 --> 00:49:38,371
has solidified the position of the provisional government.

663
00:49:39,301 --> 00:49:42,341
Sadly, the plan to assassinate the Japanese minister has failed,

664
00:49:43,201 --> 00:49:45,641
but it showed how determined we are to fight for independence.

665
00:49:46,841 --> 00:49:50,171
We, at Joseon Youth Alliance, should work harder as well.

666
00:49:51,741 --> 00:49:55,041
You should continue working as the head secretary at Office of Records.

667
00:49:55,041 --> 00:49:56,241
We need you in that position...

668
00:49:56,241 --> 00:49:58,571
to figure out how much assets those high-ranking officials have.

669
00:49:58,941 --> 00:50:02,171
All right. But I can't do it for a long time.

670
00:50:02,601 --> 00:50:06,041
Having to flatter those officials is eating me up inside.

671
00:50:06,401 --> 00:50:07,501
Mr. Yang,

672
00:50:08,001 --> 00:50:11,401
I heard that you've been frequenting the stock exchange.

673
00:50:11,771 --> 00:50:13,641
You could ruin everything for you and your family,

674
00:50:14,041 --> 00:50:15,141
so you should stop going there.

675
00:50:17,841 --> 00:50:18,871
All right.

676
00:50:38,801 --> 00:50:42,001
Hey, Brother! Gosh, I looked everywhere for you.

677
00:50:43,841 --> 00:50:46,701
We have a big problem. Libera is fighting with a customer.

678
00:50:46,741 --> 00:50:49,271
- Oh, okay. 
- The customer is holding...

679
00:50:49,401 --> 00:50:51,771
a barrel of oil, saying he'd set the entire bar on fire.

680
00:50:51,871 --> 00:50:53,471
All right. Wait for me there.

681
00:50:54,071 --> 00:50:56,341
Gosh, you don't have time to waste like this.

682
00:50:56,471 --> 00:50:57,801
What are you even doing here?

683
00:50:57,901 --> 00:50:59,241
- Hurry up. 
- Okay.

684
00:51:07,401 --> 00:51:08,471
Yul...

685
00:51:10,271 --> 00:51:11,571
didn't go home, right?

686
00:51:16,071 --> 00:51:17,801
He's in there, isn't he?

687
00:51:18,801 --> 00:51:21,471
We'll soon receive instructions for the next step.

688
00:51:21,471 --> 00:51:23,941
Until then, please do your best in your positions.

689
00:51:24,301 --> 00:51:27,141
By the way, when will we get to meet the head in person?

690
00:51:27,571 --> 00:51:29,171
Our organization was formed a year ago.

691
00:51:29,171 --> 00:51:31,941
Shouldn't he at least show us his face as our comrade?

692
00:51:32,341 --> 00:51:33,441
He's right.

693
00:51:33,801 --> 00:51:36,541
We can't keep following orders from someone whom we don't even know.

694
00:51:36,741 --> 00:51:38,871
He'll reveal himself when the right time comes.

695
00:51:39,241 --> 00:51:40,301
Soon, we will...

696
00:52:28,141 --> 00:52:29,201
You...

697
00:52:30,741 --> 00:52:31,771
I want in too.

698
00:52:32,771 --> 00:52:35,071
- What? 
- If you don't let me join you,

699
00:52:36,041 --> 00:52:39,401
I'll run to Jongno Police Station and tell the police everything.

700
00:52:40,741 --> 00:52:43,641
I know him. You can drop your guns.

701
00:52:45,141 --> 00:52:46,371
I told you to drop your guns!

702
00:52:57,701 --> 00:52:59,071
I'll sort this out.

703
00:53:00,501 --> 00:53:02,001
All of you should leave now.

704
00:53:26,301 --> 00:53:27,541
What do you think you're doing?

705
00:53:27,671 --> 00:53:31,741
I've been wondering where all the money from Carpe Diem was going to.

706
00:53:32,601 --> 00:53:33,901
You've been supporting the rebel forces.

707
00:53:34,501 --> 00:53:36,641
Do you even know what we're trying to do?

708
00:53:38,001 --> 00:53:39,001
I do.

709
00:53:40,401 --> 00:53:42,401
You're trying to teach Japan a lesson.

710
00:53:47,041 --> 00:53:48,941
Teach me how to shoot a gun.

711
00:53:49,801 --> 00:53:52,941
I'll put bullet holes through the heads of those who killed my dad.

712
00:53:53,341 --> 00:53:56,071
I can't teach you if it's for vengeance. I absolutely can't.

713
00:53:56,071 --> 00:53:58,771
I'll be avenging my nation by avenging my father's death.

714
00:53:59,071 --> 00:54:00,441
Let me fight too.

715
00:54:06,771 --> 00:54:08,141
I don't have the authority to do so.

716
00:54:12,241 --> 00:54:13,271
Okay.

717
00:54:14,401 --> 00:54:16,471
Then I'll head over to Jongno Police Station...

718
00:54:22,301 --> 00:54:24,901
I'll ask the head of our organization, but...

719
00:54:26,941 --> 00:54:28,001
Mark my words.

720
00:54:28,741 --> 00:54:32,871
If you talk about what you saw here today, I won't forgive you.

721
00:54:37,471 --> 00:54:38,771
Just go get his permission.

722
00:54:40,801 --> 00:54:42,901
I'm ready to sacrifice my life.

723
00:54:59,541 --> 00:55:01,241
We did let our guards down.

724
00:55:01,701 --> 00:55:05,071
I also think she's been keeping an eye on us for a long time.

725
00:55:09,701 --> 00:55:11,041
What should we do, Boss?

726
00:55:14,841 --> 00:55:16,241
Did you hear me, sir?

727
00:55:19,441 --> 00:55:23,071
If she's willing to make effort and has the talent,

728
00:55:24,341 --> 00:55:26,141
it wouldn't be bad to groom her into a sniper.

729
00:55:28,071 --> 00:55:29,201
Do you really mean it?

730
00:55:29,501 --> 00:55:32,771
A female sniper would be useful for disguise purposes.

731
00:55:33,241 --> 00:55:36,471
If she's that enthusiastic, she'll give impetus to our endeavors.

732
00:55:39,741 --> 00:55:41,601
She looks like a tomboy,

733
00:55:43,371 --> 00:55:44,671
but she's still a weak woman.

734
00:55:46,201 --> 00:55:47,341
Won't it be too risky?

735
00:55:48,241 --> 00:55:50,201
Weak? You think she's weak?

736
00:55:51,671 --> 00:55:53,471
She'll do a great job.

737
00:55:54,041 --> 00:55:55,071
Who knows?

738
00:55:55,441 --> 00:55:58,301
She might become another deadly sniper.

739
00:56:02,941 --> 00:56:03,971
Then...

740
00:56:05,841 --> 00:56:09,271
are you saying the person who made her shoot...

741
00:56:10,741 --> 00:56:12,141
was me?

742
00:56:14,201 --> 00:56:15,201
Yes.

743
00:56:16,141 --> 00:56:19,301
That means the person who gave her trauma...

744
00:56:19,901 --> 00:56:21,441
of guns...

745
00:56:25,041 --> 00:56:26,401
It was also me.

746
00:56:30,201 --> 00:56:31,271
Hey.

747
00:56:32,041 --> 00:56:34,871
Don't you think she'll become pretty useful with a bit of training?

748
00:56:36,341 --> 00:56:38,371
She learns everything very quickly.

749
00:56:39,541 --> 00:56:40,571
I'm done.

750
00:56:41,701 --> 00:56:42,741
20 seconds.

751
00:56:43,401 --> 00:56:45,071
Do you know what this gun's nickname is?

752
00:56:45,741 --> 00:56:48,841
Because its gunshot is similar to a typewriter sound,

753
00:56:48,841 --> 00:56:50,341
it got the nickname "Chicago Typewriter".

754
00:56:50,771 --> 00:56:51,801
So what?

755
00:56:51,871 --> 00:56:53,301
You should write something good.

756
00:56:54,001 --> 00:56:57,071
Don't write to gain fame and women.

757
00:56:57,171 --> 00:56:58,971
Write something magnificent.

758
00:57:04,801 --> 00:57:06,801
Mr. Han, are you okay?

759
00:57:08,071 --> 00:57:09,271
By any chance,

760
00:57:10,671 --> 00:57:14,501
did Seol kill someone she shouldn't have killed in her past life...

761
00:57:16,641 --> 00:57:18,671
because of Hui Young's command?

762
00:57:19,941 --> 00:57:22,971
That's... I don't know either.

763
00:57:24,641 --> 00:57:25,671
Then...

764
00:57:28,141 --> 00:57:30,801
Su Hyeon must've gotten shot by a gun that time...

765
00:57:33,341 --> 00:57:34,501
because of me.

766
00:57:50,141 --> 00:57:51,301
Do you have the time?

767
00:57:58,601 --> 00:57:59,641
It's 12pm.

768
00:58:00,341 --> 00:58:01,901
When will Jung Gil go back?

769
00:58:03,071 --> 00:58:04,671
It'll probably be tomorrow.

770
00:58:05,741 --> 00:58:06,801
Thank you.

771
00:58:09,501 --> 00:58:11,871
Yoon Jung Gil will leave in 10 minutes. Hurry up.

772
00:58:13,841 --> 00:58:16,641
I told you to write something magnificent.

773
00:58:17,141 --> 00:58:21,071
Publishing that third-rate novel is a waste of newspaper space.

774
00:58:22,441 --> 00:58:23,941
Hey, Su Hyeon!

775
00:58:51,441 --> 00:58:53,501
At 10pm on April 19.

776
00:58:53,941 --> 00:58:56,041
The target is Min Hwan Shik at Namdaemun.

777
00:58:56,141 --> 00:58:58,771
Ryu Su Hyeon and Jang Ki Bong will be the sniper team.

778
00:58:59,201 --> 00:59:03,071
Yang Hyung Shik and Choi Mong Gyu will deliver the goods.

779
00:59:03,541 --> 00:59:06,441
Other comrades must secure an escape route.

780
00:59:07,371 --> 00:59:10,401
This is Su Hyeon's first mission. Will she be okay?

781
00:59:11,971 --> 00:59:14,841
She has to pull it off in order for us to accept her as our comrade.

782
00:59:21,741 --> 00:59:22,801
Did they fail?

783
00:59:23,371 --> 00:59:25,201
The escape route is this way.

784
00:59:26,971 --> 00:59:28,341
It's that way. Get him!

785
00:59:32,741 --> 00:59:34,771
What are you doing? You should run. Do you want to die?

786
00:59:49,941 --> 00:59:50,941
Hurry up. Run.

787
00:59:58,771 --> 00:59:59,771
Over there!

788
01:00:00,201 --> 01:00:01,241
Follow them!

789
01:00:08,001 --> 01:00:09,001
This way.

790
01:00:13,671 --> 01:00:14,771
What are you doing?

791
01:00:14,971 --> 01:00:16,341
If you don't want to die, be quiet.

792
01:00:42,171 --> 01:00:43,171
It's you.

793
01:00:45,401 --> 01:00:46,941
You're the masked man who saved me.

794
01:00:51,801 --> 01:00:53,001
What are you talking about?

795
01:00:58,941 --> 01:01:02,041
Where have they gone? I told you to keep eyes on them!

796
01:01:02,041 --> 01:01:05,571
Instead of writing cheap romance novels,

797
01:01:06,801 --> 01:01:08,741
why don't you do something that helps our country like this?

798
01:02:34,601 --> 01:02:37,341
(Chicago Typewriter)

